DIGEST
SB 437 Original 2026 Regular Session Abraham
Present law provides for the regulation of facilities that are not otherwise required to be
licensed by the La. Dept. of Health or the Dept. of Children and Family Services, that
provide housing or temporary residence for individuals who have been arrested for the
commission of a crime, and who are referred by a judicial agency.
Present law prohibits a facility from providing treatment to an individual and a judicial
agency from referring an individual to a facility providing treatment until the La. Dept. of
Health has adopted rules and certified that the facility is in compliance with its rules.
Proposed law repeals present law requirements for La. Dept. of Health approval.
Proposed law prohibits a facility from providing residential substance use treatment to any
individual, unless the facility is licensed by the La. Dept. of Health as a behavioral health
